The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 May is 41,997 (4,860.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 May, there were 130 new confirmed cases (15.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 April, there were 123 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 6% (7 extra cases).
